Costs in the interactive dependency resolver


Costs and cost components

The cost of a solution produced by the interactive dependency resolver is a
value that aptitude uses to determine how Â«Â badÂ Â» that solution is.
Solutions that are Â«Â betterÂ Â» are always displayed before solutions that are
Â«Â worseÂ Â». The cost of solutions is defined in the configuration option
Aptitude::ProblemResolver::SolutionCost.

Some typical costs are shown in ExempleÂ 2.1, Â«Â Sample resolver costsÂ Â».

ExempleÂ 2.1.Â Sample resolver costs

